  "local_port": 55016,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Can I apply for a PR in Australia while I am studying in Australia for a masters course on a student visa 573? I have met the criteria of 65 points.",
  "response": "Yes, you can apply for Permanent Residency (PR) in Australia while studying on a Student Visa (Subclass 573 or now part of Subclass 500), provided you meet the eligibility criteria for the PR visa you are applying for. Having met the 65-point threshold is a good start, but there are other factors to consider:\n\n### Key Points to Consider:\n1. **PR Visa Pathways**:  \n   The most common PR pathways for international students include:\n   - **Skilled Independent Visa (Subclass 189)**: Points-tested stream.\n   - **Skilled Nominated Visa (Subclass 190)**: Requires nomination by an Australian state or territory.\n   - **Skilled Work Regional (Provisional) Visa (Subclass 491)**: For regional areas, requires state or family nomination.\n\n2. **Eligibility Criteria**:  \n   - **Skills Assessment**: You must complete a skills assessment in your nominated occupation from the relevant assessing authority.  \n   - **English Language Proficiency**: You must meet the English language requirements (e.g., IELTS, PTE, or TOEFL).  \n   - **Age**: You must be under 45 years old at the time of application.  \n   - **Health and Character**: You must meet health and character requirements.  \n\n3. **Occupation on the Skills List**:  \n   Your occupation must be on the relevant skilled occupation list (e.g., Medium and Long-term Strategic Skills List (MLTSSL) for Subclass 189 or the Short-term Skilled Occupation List (STSOL) for Subclass 190).  \n\n4. **Study and PR Application**:  \n   You can apply for PR while studying, but you must ensure that you meet all the requirements for the PR visa. Additionally, completing your master's degree in Australia may help you earn extra points for your PR application (e.g., Australian study requirement, points for qualifications).  \n\n5. **Bridging Visa**:  \n   If your student visa expires while your PR application is being processed, you may be eligible for a Bridging Visa A (BVA) to stay in Australia lawfully while waiting for the outcome.  \n\n### Steps to Take:\n1. Check your eligibility for a PR visa based on your points, occupation, and other criteria.  \n2. Obtain a skills assessment for your nominated occupation.  \n3. Submit an Expression of Interest (EOI) through SkillSelect for Subclass 189, 190, or 491.  \n4. If invited, lodge your PR visa application.  \n\n### Points Breakdown:  \nSince you mentioned you have met the 65-point threshold, ensure you have accurately calculated your points based on:  \n- Age  \n- English language proficiency  \n- Australian study requirement  \n- Skilled employment experience  \n- Education qualifications (e.g., master's degree)  \n- Other factors (e.g., partner skills, regional study, etc.).  \n\n### Final Note:  \nWhile you can apply for PR while on a student visa, it\u2019s essential to ensure you maintain your student visa obligations until your PR visa is granted. You may also seek advice from a registered migration agent to guide you through the process.  \n\nGood luck with your application!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
